RSF membership goes by your expected graduation date, so if it's too early, you'll be denied access until you fix it.

(Which is completely dumb, since they obviously know whether you're enrolled or not that semester, but 'tis Berkeley...)
Nothing really, other than automatically putting you on the degree list for that semester.

I was a spring admit in January 2018 so my graduation date on CalCentral shows Fall 2021. However, based on my schedule plan I will almost certainly graduate in Spring 2021. Is there any benefit to updating this graduation date now? What exactly does changing this date do?
history.subject: What is the benefit of changing your graduation date?
